			<common:synonyms xml:lang="en">Solar Panel Waste; End-of-Life Panels</common:synonyms>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification>
					<common:category level="0">End-of-life treatment</common:category>
					<common:category level="1">Material recycling</common:category>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">As the solar photovoltaic (PV) market grows, the volume of end-of-life panels will also increase. By 2030, the United States is expected to have as much as one million total tons of solar panel waste. Some rare elements in PV cells, like gallium and indium, are being depleted from the environment over time. Most PV panel waste ends up in landfill, making policy actions necessary to address the challenges of solar PV waste.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">随着太阳能光伏（PV）市场的发展，报废电池板的数量也将增加。预计到 2030 年，美国的太阳能电池板废料总量将高达 100 万吨。随着时间的推移，光伏电池中的一些稀有元素，如镓和铟，正在从环境中消耗殆尽。大多数光伏电池板废料最终被填埋，因此有必要采取政策行动来应对太阳能光伏电池废料带来的挑战。</common:generalComment>
